  "doc_id": "3578",
  "text": "Witherden et al. [CITATION_1] recently reported that either an AAA or AAG codon at positions 1576-1578 of the ftsI gene could encode the N526K substitution, and both codon types were identified in the NTHi and H. haemolyticus gBLNAR and gBLPACR isolates in this study. Interestingly, all isolates of both species with both the A502V and N526K substitutions (designated as group IIb by Dabernat et al. [CITATION_2] ) had the N526K substitution encoded by the AAA triplet. However, further studies need to be performed to evaluate the significance of this observation.",
